Reebok Question Mid Pink Toe (GS)
results.story: The Reebok Question Mid Big Kid ‘Pink Toe’ gives Allen Iverson’s debut signature shoe a pastel makeover. The mid-top is clad in pristine white leather with subtle pink accents, including a suede toe cap and Reebok’s Vector logo embroidered on the quarter panel. Lightweight cushioning arrives via a sculpted EVA midsole with visible Hexalite cushioning in the forefoot and heel. Underfoot, a darker shade of pink distinguishes the translucent rubber outsole.

results.name: Reebok Zig Kinetica Ghostbusters Stay Puft Marshmallow Man (GS)
results.story: Offered in grade school sizing, the Reebok Zig Kinetica J ‘Mr. Stay-Puft’ celebrates the release of ‘Ghostbusters: Afterlife,’ the fourth installment in the supernatural comedy franchise. The film’s Mini-Puft characters are depicted in an all-over graphic print that embellishes the structured white textile upper, which is mounted on a Floatride Fuel midsole wrapped in an energy-returning Zig Energy Shell. The iconic Ghostbusters logo adorns the tongue, while Reebok’s Vector trademark is embossed on the lateral heel.

results.name: Reebok Zig Dynamica Jurassic Park (GS)
results.story: The Jurassic Park x Reebok Zig Dynamica Alt Big Kid ‘Night Vision Goggles’ is drawn from an expansive collection centered around the 1993 blockbuster film. This pair features a seamless mesh upper covered in swirling green hues in a nod to Tim Murphy’s night vision goggles. The iconic Jurassic Park logo decorates the tongue, while webbing pull tabs at the heel display mismatched Jurassic Park and Reebok branding. The sneaker rides on a contrasting black FuelFoam midsole, good for responsive cushioning and a smooth ride.

results.name: Reebok Kamikaze II NERF NERFOOP (GS)
results.story: Offered in grade school sizing, the NERF x Reebok Kamikaze 2 J ‘Backboard Breaker’ showcases asymmetrical color blocking on the vintage hoops shoe made famous by Shawn Kemp. The unique design, inspired by the Nerfoop Big Bad Backboard from the ‘90s, features a leather and nubuck upper in an array of vibrant hues, including lime green, fuchsia, yellow, orange and powder blue. NERF branding lands on the tongue tag and lateral forefoot, while a paint splatter effect decorates the heel. The mid-top rides on a multicolor EVA midsole with Reebok’s Hexalite cushioning.

Reebok Question Mid Yellow Toe (GS)
results.story: Made for grade schoolers, the Reebok Question Mid GS ‘Yellow Toe’ is based on a PE colorway that Kobe Bryant famously wore during the 2002 – 2003 NBA season, remembered as the athlete’s period of sneaker free agency. Allen Iverson’s debut signature shoe is incongruously dressed in the Lakers’ signature hues, highlighted by a white tumbled leather upper with a yellow leather toe cap. Contrasting purple accents land on the sneaker’s branding elements, including embroidered Vector logos and ‘Reebok’ spelled out on the TPU eyelets.

results.name: Reebok Question Mid 76ers Bred (GS)
results.story: Built for big kids, the Reebok Question Mid J ‘Street Sleigh’ presents a two-tone colorway of Allen Iverson’s debut signature shoe, highlighted by a black leather upper with red patent leather on the mudguard and toe cap. A matching red finish coats the EVA midsole, equipped with visible Hexalite cushioning in the heel and forefoot. Underfoot, smoky rubber is used on the outsole, featuring cutaway detailing under the heel for another window into the sneaker’s Hexalite technology.

results.name: Reebok Cardi Club C Red (GS)
results.story: Offered in grade school sizing, the Cardi B x Reebok Club C J ‘Red Clear’ is taken from a capsule collection developed in tandem with the Bronx-born rapper. The retro tennis shoe from 1985 is reborn as a fashion-forward silhouette dressed heel to toe in scarlet patent leather. A pull loop atop the exposed foam tongue delivers easy on and off, while transparent quarter panels add a see-through element to the monochromatic design. A bulky midsole is similarly treated to a translucent finish.

results.name: Reebok Cardi Club C Double Red (GS)
results.story: Made for big kids, the Cardi B x Reebok Club C J ‘Instinct Red’ is drawn from a capsule collection developed in partnership with the chart-topping hip hop star. The vintage tennis shoe is given an eye-catching makeover, highlighted by a glossy patent leather upper in a bold one-note color scheme. Reebok branding is embossed on transparent TPU detailing on the tongue, heel tab and quarter panel. A rubber cupsole in the same scarlet finish anchors the low-profile silhouette.

results.name: Reebok Cardi Club C Double Black (GS)
results.story: Built for big kids, the Cardi B x Reebok Club C J ‘Triple Black’ is included in a capsule collection created in partnership with the Bronx-born rapper. The vintage silhouette, originally released in the ‘80s as a performance tennis shoe, receives a sleek makeover that combines a monochrome black finish with a shiny patent leather build. The low-top is mounted on a durable rubber cupsole, featuring a visible EVA wedge on the medial sidewall for cushioned comfort.

Reebok Club C 85 DC Wonder Woman (GS)
results.story: Launching as part of a capsule collection celebrating the superhero film, the Wonder Woman 1984 x Reebok Club C 85 Big Kid ‘Air Flight’ draws inspiration from the titular character’s invisible plane, highlighted by an iridescent silver finish on a coated leather upper. A graphic print displaying fluffy white clouds and blue skies covers the tongue, while Wonder Woman’s ‘WW’ logo adorns the glossy red heel tab.

results.name: Reebok Question Mid Red Toe 25th Anniversary (GS)
results.story: The 2020 edition of the Reebok Question Mid OG GS ‘Red Toe’ brings back the inaugural colorway of Allen Iverson’s debut signature shoe. Releasing just shy of the sneaker’s 25th anniversary, the mid-top is distinguished by a red suede toe cap, an original detail that survived the first 5,000 pairs before it was replaced by pearlized red leather. Additional OG details include Question branding on the heel tab, visible Hexalite cushioning and an icy blue translucent outsole.

Reebok Question Low Patent Toe Carolina (GS)
results.story: Offered in grade-school sizing, the Reebok Question Patent Low J ‘Fluid Blue’ updates Allen Iverson’s debut signature shoe with a simple two-tone color scheme. The white leather upper is accented with powder blue patent leather detailing at the toe cap and heel tab, the latter marked with the traditional Question logo in white embroidery. An EVA midsole with visible Hexalite cushioning rides on an icy translucent rubber outsole for durable traction.

Reebok Classic Leather Kendrick Lamar Deconstructed (GS)
results.story: Musician Kendrick Lamar and Reebok collaborated with Garbstore designer Ian Paley for this summer 2016 ‘Split Personality’ take on the Reebok Classic Leather. Like the full adult version, this grade-school sized model features a premium Skull Grey suede upper with an Off-White midsole and a gum rubber outsole. Kendrick’s calls for unity between the Bloods and the Crips is symbolized by the red accents on the left shoe’s lateral side, and royal blue accents on the right lateral side. The unique split design also features stitched seams that run down the middle of each shoe, creating a neutral-colored middle ground on the sneaker’s medial section. Reebok logo patches on the lateral side featuring whited out lettering save for the ‘k’ for Kendrick complete the look.

results.name: Reebok Classic Leather Red and Blue (GS)
results.story: Compton-born rapper Kendrick Lamar partnered with Reebok in 2016 for this grade-school sized Kendrick Lamar x Reebok Classic GS ‘Neutral.' It features a grey suede upper, rope laces, white midsole, Kendrick’s signature on the insole, and a gum rubber outsole. The collaboration with the Compton rapper also nods to his attempts to broker peace between the Crips and Bloods with “BLUE” and “RED” embossed on the heels and “NEUTRAL” branded under the tongue.

results.name: Reebok Ventilator Naked Splash (GS)
results.story: Originally released in 1990, the Reebok Ventilator features a mesh ventilation system on the side panels. In 2015, Danish women’s sneaker store Naked teamed up with Reebok for their own take on the classic silhouette. The premium white leather upper is given allover black speckled detailing, supported underfoot by a white IMEVA midsole with Hexalite cushioning technology. The high-abrasion rubber outsole emerges in Mint Glo.

Reebok Kamikaze II Mid Easter (2014) (GS)
results.story: Shawn Kemp’s second signature sneaker, the Kamikaze 2, debuted in 1995 and became one of Reebok’s most popular basketball shoes following the Pump era. Celebrating the arrival of spring, the brand re-released the 90s model in April 2014. The Reebok Kamikaze 2 Mid Big Kids 'Easter' sneaker models itself after the adult version, reinterpreting it for kids' wear. The shoe sports a perforated suede upper in shades of teal and a butter-yellow lining.
